What is a Set?




🎯 Definition: A collection of things that share common characteristics. They can be elements, members, objects or similar terms.
Examples:

Set of even numbers:

{2, 4, 6, 8, …}

Set of vowels: {a, e, i, o, u}

Permutations of \(r\) Objects from \(n\)









Key Formula


\(P(n,r)\) or \(_nP_r\): Number of ways to arrange \(r\) objects selected from \(n\) distinct objects
\[P(n,r) = \frac{n!}{(n-r)!}\]













Note


\[
P_{k,n} =
\frac{n!}{(n-k)!}
=
\]
\[
= \frac{
  n(n-1)\cdots(n-k+1)\,
  \overbrace{(n-k)(n-k-1)\cdots3\cdot2\cdot1}^{(n-k)!}
}{
  (n-k)!
}
\]
\[
= \underbrace{
n (n-1) (n-2) \cdots (n-k+1)
}_{k \text{ terms}}
\]
Fill in \(k\) slots with no repetitions
\[
\underbrace{n \; (n-1) \; \_ \; \_ \; \cdots}_{k}
\]
Note that if we allowed repetitions we would get \(n^k\) \[
\underbrace{n \; n \; n \; \cdots \; n}_{k}
\]
